name: disarmament-treaties-database
notes:
Since 1978, the United Nations has been publishing the status of multilateral Arms Regulation and Disarmament Agreements, presenting data on signatories, parties of relevant agreements and the texts of the agreements themselves.

Disarmament Treaties included:
1925 Geneva Protocol
Antarctic Treaty
Bangkok Treaty
Biological Weapons Convention
Chemical Weapons Convention
Comprehensive Nuclear-Test-Ban Treaty
Convention on Certain Conventional Weapons
Convention on Cluster Munitions	
Convention on Environmental Modification Techniques (ENMOD)
Inter-American Convention on Firearms
Inter-American Convention on Transparency
Kinshasa Convention
Mine Ban Convention
Moon Treaty (Celestial Bodies)
Outer Space Treaty
Partial Test Ban Treaty
Pelindaba Treaty
Sea-Bed Treaty
Treaty of Rarotonga
Treaty of Tlatelolco
Treaty on a Nuclear-Weapon-Free Zone in Central Asia (CANWFZ)
Treaty on Conventional Armed Forces in Europe (CFE)
Treaty on Open Skies
Treaty on the Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons (NPT)
title: Disarmament Treaties Database
